author: Written by: Sam Winstrom, Assignment Editor
title: SLIDESHOW: Early voting locations in Southeast Louisiana
text:
NEW ORLEANS (WVUE) - Early voting for Louisiana's Oct. 24 election kicks off today.
Voters will be able to vote in several locations across the New Orleans Metro Area between 8:30 a.m. and 6 p.m. until Oct. 17 (excluding Sunday, Oct. 11).
Check out a sample ballot for your parish from the Secretary of State's website and find your nearest polling location in the slideshow above.
